('Sabaton', 'Attero Dominatus', 'Attero Dominatus is the third album by Swedish power metal band Sabaton, as well as the first to feature keyboardist Daniel Mÿhr.\nThe Latin name is intended to mean \'Destroy Tyranny\' (lit. \'Wear down absolute authority\'). However it is syntactically incorrect. The imperative verb conjugation should be used in conjunction with the accusative noun form to accurately translate to the command- thus, Attere Dominatum, or Atterete if it is addressed to more than one person.\nAs with the Primo Victoria album, the lyrics on Attero Dominatus deals with different war subjects. \"Nuclear Attack\" deals with the atomic bombings of Hiroshima and Nagasaki, \"Rise of Evil\" with the rise of the Third Reich and Adolf Hitler. The song \"Back in Control\" deals with the Falklands War. \"In the Name of God\" takes on the situation in the middle-east by tackling suicide bombers and everyone who kill innocent people in the name of their god.\nA video was shot for the titletrack in Umeå, Sweden done by Nocturnal Rites\' drummer Owe Lingvall.', 'https://www.metal-archives.com/images/1/1/8/9/118953.jpg?5410', 'Estudio', 'SI', '2006', '7', '28', NULL, '', '', 240058),
('Sabaton', 'Biskmarck EP', '', '', 'Estudio', 'SI', '2019', NULL, NULL, NULL, '', '', 0),
('Sabaton', 'Carolus Rex', 'Carolus Rex is the seventh studio album by Swedish heavy metal band Sabaton. It was released with both English/mixed and Swedish vocals. It would also be the last album to feature guitarists Oskar Montelius and Rikard Sundén, drummer Daniel Mullback and keyboardist Daniel Mÿhr. It was produced by Peter Tägtgren in Abyss Studios.', 'https://www.metal-archives.com/images/4/1/4/3/414359.jpg?1806', 'Estudio', 'SI', '2012', '5', '25', NULL, '', '', 270009),
('Sabaton', 'Coat of Arms', 'Coat of Arms is the fifth studio album by Swedish heavy metal band Sabaton. All music by Joakim Brodén and all lyrics by Brodén and Pär Sundström (except lyrics on \"Saboteurs\" and \"Midway\" by Sundström only and lyrics on \"Metal Ripper\" and \"Wehrmacht\" by Brodén only).', 'https://www.metal-archives.com/images/2/6/7/0/267024.jpg?1026', 'Estudio', 'SI', '2010', '5', '21', NULL, '', '', 234053),
('Sabaton', 'Heroes', 'Heroes is the seventh studio album by Swedish heavy metal band Sabaton. It was released on 6 May 2014. It is the first album to feature the new Sabaton line-up with guitarists Chris Rörland and Thobbe Englund, as well as new drummer Hannes van Dahl. It was produced by Peter Tägtgren in Abyss Studios. The artwork was made by Péter Sallai and the photos were created by Ryan Garrison. The first single To Hell and Back from their album was released digitally on 14 March 2014 and available on iTunes, Nuclear Blast, Amazon and Google Play. The second single Resist And Bite was also released digitally on 2 May 2014, available on iTunes, Nuclear Blast and Amazon.', 'https://www.metal-archives.com/images/4/0/3/1/403118.jpg?5832', 'Estudio', 'SI', '2014', '5', '16', NULL, '', '', 216057),
('Sabaton', 'Primo Victoria', 'Primo Victoria (Latin \"Victory first\") is the second album by Swedish power metal band Sabaton. This was the first album they released for their new label, Black Lodge Records. The band was commissioned by members of the Norwegian Army 2nd Battalion to make an alternative version of Panzer Battalion. The alternate version, called Second Battalion, differs only in that the lyric \"Second Battalion\" is sung in place of \"panzer battalion\".', 'https://www.metal-archives.com/images/6/8/4/4/68440.jpg?4855', 'Estudio', 'SI', '2005', '3', '4', NULL, '', '', 246005),
('Sabaton', 'The Art of War', 'The Art of War is the fourth album by Swedish heavy metal band Sabaton. The lyrics of the songs are about famous battles or war, mostly based on the battles of the First and Second World Wars or based on the The Art of War by Sun Tzu, for which the album is named.', 'https://www.metal-archives.com/images/1/9/0/5/190522.jpg?3353', 'Estudio', 'SI', '2008', '5', '30', NULL, '', '', 294028),
